{{Infobox language |name=Basa-Kontagora |altname= |nativename= |states=[[Nigeria]] |region=[[Kontagora]] |ethnicity=30,000 (no date)<ref name=e15>{{e15|bsr}}</ref> |speakers=10 |date=1987 |ref = e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo languages|Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo languages|Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Kainji languages|Kainji]] |fam5=[[Basa languages]] |fam6=Kontagora–Gumna |iso3=bsr |glotto=bass1259 |glottorefname=Bassa-Kontagora }}
'''Basa-Kontagora''' is a nearly extinct [[Kainji language]] of [[Nigeria]]. It is spoken in [[Mariga, Nigeria|Mariga]], [[Niger State]], near [[Kontagora]] and the [[Basa languages|Basa]] homeland.
