===Verb===
Kartvelian verbs can indicate one, two, or three [[grammatical person]]s. A performer of an action is called the [[Subject (grammar)|subject]] and affected persons are objects ([[direct object|direct]] or [[indirect object|indirect]]). The person may be singular or plural. According to the number of persons, the verbs are classified as unipersonal, bipersonal or tripersonal.

*Unipersonal verbs have only a subject and so are always intransitive.
*Bipersonal verbs have a subject and one object, which can be ''direct'' or ''indirect''. The verb is:
**transitive when the object is ''direct'';
**intransitive if the object is ''indirect''.
*Tripersonal verbs have one subject and both ''direct'' and ''indirect'' objects and are ditransitive.

